    "• To post-process output data once jobs are done on worker nodes.",
    "• To take actions on jobs according to various timeout configurations or user commands.",
    "• To report job states to JEDI if those jobs were generated by JEDI.The PanDA server scales horizontally by adding instances since Web servers are stateless and time-based processes are fine-grained.",
    "Figure 3 below shows the architecture of a single PanDA server instance.",
    "PanDA Web applications are embedded in Web Server Gateway Interface (WSGI) [25] daemons running behind an Apache HTTP server."
